      Big Short 4 Ever
   =20
 =20
One stylized fact is that if every month you put out a client note saying =
=E2=80=9CTHE MARKET WILL CRASH,=E2=80=9D and for like 10 years the market d=
oes not crash, and then at the end of the 10 years there=E2=80=99s a huge c=
rash, then for the next, like, 30 years you will be able to go on televisio=
n above the chyron =E2=80=9CGUY WHO CALLED THE MARKET CRASH HAS THOUGHTS,=
=E2=80=9D which is nice for you. For some reason being right about a crash =
once outweighs being wrong about it any number of times.=C2=A0=E2=80=9CBein=
g early is the same as being wrong,=E2=80=9D is a thing that people in fina=
ncial markets sometimes say, but rarely to=C2=A0TV bookers.Separately thoug=
h what if you are just bopping along being long sometimes and short sometim=
es, being optimistic sometimes and pessimistic other times, whatever seems =
to you to be justified by the data, getting some calls right and other call=
s wrong, mostly making money for your clients but sometimes losing money fo=
r them, and then one day you think things look bad and position yourself ve=
ry short and then a week later there=E2=80=99s a huge crash? You will also =
get at least 30 years of =E2=80=9CGUY WHO CALLED THE MARKET CRASH HAS THOUG=
HTS,=E2=80=9D and in a sense you will deserve it more than the perma-bear d=
id. But getting all that attention might change you;=C2=A0the psychic rewar=
ds of being bearish=C2=A0right before the crash might be so lavish that you=
=C2=A0find yourself constantly chasing that thrill. Also just =E2=80=9CThin=
g Is Bubble=E2=80=9D is better television than =E2=80=9CThing Pretty Good=
=E2=80=9D:TV host: Today we have on our program=C2=A0a guy who was Big Shor=
t before=C2=A0the market crashed.You: Thanks for having me. I wanted to tal=
k about this biotech company that I=E2=80=99m really bullish on, I think th=
ey=E2=80=99re doing great work and are about to announce a cure for=E2=80=
=94=C2=A0TV host: Sorry aren=E2=80=99t you a Big Short guy?You: Yes I did p=
osition myself short leading up to the financial crisis because certain ind=
icators=E2=80=94TV host: Are you Big Short anything right now?You: No I =E2=
=80=A6=C2=A0I=C2=A0like this biotech a lot?TV host: Big Short! Big Short! B=
ig Short!You: I=E2=80=99m sorry I don=E2=80=99t have any short ideas prepar=
ed.TV host: Surely you dislike something?You: A stock?TV host: Anything, we=
=E2=80=99re not picky.You: I =E2=80=A6=C2=A0uh =E2=80=A6=C2=A0I don=E2=80=
=99t know, those robocalls that are like =E2=80=9Cwe are calling with impor=
tant information about your warranty,=E2=80=9D those=C2=A0are pretty annoyi=
ng?TV host: There you have it folks, the Big Short guy=E2=80=99s next crusa=
de is robocalls!And then the next day there are a dozen stories like =E2=80=
=9CBig Short Guy Now Big Short Robocalls=E2=80=9D and you get to go on TV s=
ome more. After more than a decade of that do you maybe stop bothering with=
 long theses? Do you just go on TV to be like =E2=80=9Cyou know what really=
 honks me off is the=C2=A0Federal Reserve. And what=E2=80=99s the deal with=
=C2=A0NFTs?=E2=80=9DAnyway here=E2=80=99s an article titled =E2=80=9CWhy th=
e =E2=80=98Big Short=E2=80=99 Guys Think Bitcoin Is a Bubble,=E2=80=9D and =
you can read it for their reasons, but I=C2=A0prefer to talk about meta-rea=
sons. If they didn=E2=80=99t think it was a bubble you wouldn=E2=80=99t be =
reading it!
