<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Boredom markets hypothesis</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Last April <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25381248.276473/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnL=
mNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDQtMzAvaWYteW91LXJlLWJvcmVkLXlvdS1jYW4t=
dHJhZGUtc3RvY2tzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMTgyMV9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWw=
mdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIxMTAxOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZX=
lzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2aec88e0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscop=
e=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> I proposed</a> that th=
e stock market was going up because people had nothing else to do, so gambl=
ing on stocks was=C2=A0<em>relatively=C2=A0</em>fun compared to their other=
 options. That still seems like as good an explanation as anything else for=
 the last year and a half of, you know, meme stocks, Dogecoin, all this. Bu=
t I do not pretend that, as a theory, it makes any especially precise predi=
ctions. In particular,=C2=A0it does not predict that there is some sort of =
boredom bubble that will eventually pop when people find other entertainmen=
ts. I wrote at the time:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you=
 believe the boredom thesis of the current retail rally, that is good news,=
 because that thesis is basically countercyclical: The worse the economy is=
, the more bored investors will be. If stocks sell off because the coronavi=
rus crisis is longer and worse than expected, there will be even fewer ente=
rtainment options and more people will turn, in desperation, to buying stoc=
ks on their phones. If someone finds a magic cure for the virus tomorrow, s=
tocks will rally and all the new retail investors will happily sell into th=
e rally at the top and go back to their other, more entertaining, entertain=
ments.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Since then the S&amp;P =
500 is up more than 50%, the economy has largely reopened and is running qu=
ite hot, professional sports are largely back to normal, you can go to rest=
aurants and gyms and casinos and bowling alleys, =E2=80=9CSuccession=E2=80=
=9D is back on, people seem to enjoy =E2=80=9CSquid Game,=E2=80=9D really t=
here is not a lot of reason to think that people are starved for any of the=
ir normal entertainments. And boredom trading might be on its way out, <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25381248.276473/aHR0cH=
M6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvZjlkNTQ2YTMtY2Q3Yy00MTliLTg0NGQtNzAzOWExZWI1M=
jk0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB943d7345" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the Financial Times reports<=
/a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are signs that the c=
ohort of thrill-seeking traders, who chased volatility in everything from t=
he tech sector to turbocharged stocks such as GameStop to cryptocurrencies,=
 have stepped back in recent months, analysts say.</p><p style=3D"margin: 1=
6px 0;">=E2=80=9CAt some point you run out of shiny new objects,=E2=80=9D s=
aid Liz Ann Sonders, chief investment strategist at Charles Schwab. She poi=
nted to =E2=80=9Cwaning interest=E2=80=9D in speculative bets on so-called =
meme stocks, which were targeted by traders on Reddit, an online forum that=
 was valued at $10bn in August.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Charles Sch=
wab, the largest retail brokerage in the US, last week reported an 8 per ce=
nt drop in trading activity in the third quarter from the second.</p><p sty=
le=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Discussions among traders on Reddit forums such as W=
allStreetBets, used by some to co-ordinate buying during the meme stock exp=
losion in the early part of the year, has declined since June, according to=
 alternative data provider Quiver Quantitative.</p></blockquote><p style=3D=
"margin: 16px 0;">Honestly it=E2=80=99s probably way too early to declare t=
he end of, you know, frantic meme-y retail trading, but I guess we can do a=
 little retrospective of the Era of Boredom Trading. It was =E2=80=A6=C2=A0=
pretty good? Like, at a high level, if you bought stocks last April you did=
 great. If you bought=C2=A0<em>GameStop Corp</em>. stock in <em>January=C2=
=A0</em>you probably have done well, unless you bought on the very hottest =
couple of days. If you bought Hertz Global Holdings Inc. stock last June wh=
en it was=C2=A0<em>in bankruptcy=C2=A0</em>you <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/25381248.276473/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLm=
NvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDUtMTIvdGhlLWhlcnR6LWdhbWJsZXJzLXdlcmUtc=
mlnaHQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTAxODIxX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291=
cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjExMDE4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/60=
7f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB4de0c17f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsc=
ope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impo=
rtant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-botto=
m-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> did surprisingly okay</a>.</p><p =
style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In a weird way, frantic meme-y retail traders wer=
e the long-term deep-value bid for stocks. The economy was good and stock p=
rices were high, and then the economy crashed shut and near-term corporate =
cash flows looked likely to be very bad, and stock prices reacted by fallin=
g, and retail investors said, =E2=80=9Cmeh, I=E2=80=99ll buy some stocks, w=
hat else do I have to do.=E2=80=9D And 18 months later the economy is good =
again and stock prices are high again and the disruption to corporate cash =
flows seems in hindsight to have been mild and short-lived. Sober professio=
nal fundamental investors turn out to have overreacted to short-term news. =
Crazed Reddit retail investors took the long view, acted as the buyer of la=
st resort when stocks were on sale, and were rewarded for it.=C2=A0</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That=E2=80=99s nice for them but also possibly eco=
nomically useful. Most of the time the stock market is primarily a sort of =
gambling venue; the idea that the stock market is a place for companies to =
raise money to fund their projects is not generally all that=C2=A0true. But=
 it=C2=A0<em>is=C2=A0</em>true in times of cash-flow crunch: If you have, s=
ay, a movie theater company with a lot of debt, and all of its movie theate=
rs shut down due to a pandemic, that company is going to be in a lot of fin=
ancial trouble. The only way out of that trouble might be for it to sell st=
ock. Traditionally, =E2=80=9Cwe have tons of debt and no cash flow and are =
going to be in big trouble if you don=E2=80=99t give us money=E2=80=9D is n=
ot a=C2=A0<em>good=C2=A0</em>stock pitch, and companies that sell stock in =
this sort of crisis often end up selling a ton of shares for not enough mon=
ey to get them through. But with bored excitable retail investors, who know=
s? Back in January, AMC Entertainment Holdings Inc. raised a ton of money i=
n a good week for meme stocks, and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/25381248.276473/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW=
9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDEtMjgva25vd2luZy13aGVuLXRvLXNlbGwtZ2FtZXN0b3Atc3RvY=
2stYXQtdGhlLXRvcC1pcy1pbXBvc3NpYmxlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDEwMTgyMV9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0=
bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIxMTAxOCZ1dG1=
fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb7db59c1" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> I w=
rote</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A week ago it was not=
 crazy to think this company was doomed; now it is entirely possible that i=
t will survive and thrive and show movies in movie theaters for decades to =
